    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-12-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <head>No. 303.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bancroft
                                Davis</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Wallace</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 23,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 27.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 30, of the 22d ultimo,
                        touching the increased duty levied on alcohol by the Turkish customs
                        authorities at Smyrna, <pb facs="0570" n="498" xml:id="pg_498"/> has been
                        received, and your action in consequence thereof meets with the Department’s
                        approval.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. C. BANCROFT DAVIS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
